WEBVTT

01:12.865 --> 01:15.701
<i>Of all my childhood memories,</i>

01:15.735 --> 01:17.770
<i>there is one sound
I remember the most.</i>

01:17.803 --> 01:20.006
<i>¡Papá!</i>

01:52.538 --> 01:54.640
<i>But if you think
we were the typical</i>

01:54.674 --> 01:56.809
<i>father and son... think again.</i>

02:21.834 --> 02:23.035
- Oh!
- Ooh.

02:27.605 --> 02:29.641
<i>Dad and I were never
bored together</i>

02:29.674 --> 02:33.545
<i>because, to my dad,
life was a big game.</i>

02:38.017 --> 02:41.887
<i>And our favorite game
was solving Dad's riddles.</i>

03:37.376 --> 03:39.044
<i>And then it happened.</i>

03:54.959 --> 03:56.928
Hey.

04:41.873 --> 04:44.142
<i>¡Mijo!</i>

05:33.024 --> 05:34.993
Oh, Renato.

06:12.163 --> 06:14.232
First of all,
I want to thank you

06:14.265 --> 06:16.033
for doing this interview.

06:16.066 --> 06:17.801
Mr. Murguia, you have built

06:17.834 --> 06:20.037
one of the most successful
aviation companies

06:20.070 --> 06:21.905
here in your hometown
of San Miguel.

06:21.939 --> 06:24.975
How did you do it? What was
the key to your success?

06:25.008 --> 06:27.978
I learned early in life
that no one's gonna help you.

06:28.011 --> 06:29.247
You got to work your ass off.

06:29.280 --> 06:30.248
And, of course,
having a brilliant CEO

06:30.281 --> 06:32.250
by my side doesn't hurt.

06:32.283 --> 06:34.818
Ay, he's saying that because
you are here.

06:34.851 --> 06:36.787
- Yes, I am. I'm kidding.
- Thank you.

06:36.820 --> 06:38.188
She's great. She's the best.

06:38.223 --> 06:40.225
I was speaking with Perla
earlier, and she mentioned

06:40.258 --> 06:42.226
you'll be expanding
into the U.S. soon.

06:44.828 --> 06:46.964
Oh, no, I think
you misunderstood her.

06:46.997 --> 06:50.133
We have no plans of doing
business in the United States.

06:50.167 --> 06:52.903
Well, why wouldn't you want
to do business with the U.S.?

06:52.936 --> 06:54.938
Uh, so h-here's the thing.

06:54.972 --> 06:57.241
Wh-Why do you guys always think

06:57.274 --> 06:59.243
the United States is
the symbol of success? Hmm?

06:59.276 --> 07:01.812
Maybe now is
a good time to take

07:01.845 --> 07:03.213
- a tour of the facility.
- No, it's a good time

07:03.247 --> 07:04.948
- to discuss this.
- Yes.

07:04.982 --> 07:06.116
Let's talk about this,
because I think there's

07:06.149 --> 07:07.985
a big problem there, you know?

07:08.018 --> 07:10.020
You want to know what the real
problem with Americans is?

07:10.053 --> 07:11.922
They're entitled.
They're ignorant.

07:11.955 --> 07:13.223
They think Mexico is just

07:13.257 --> 07:14.992
a bunch of drug cartels
and Cancún.

07:15.025 --> 07:16.994
Why don't we talk
about the planes?

07:17.027 --> 07:18.228
They're idiots.
And you know what else?

07:18.262 --> 07:19.997
- They're fat.
- Now we're all fat?

07:20.030 --> 07:22.132
- No, he means full of life.
- No, I mean full of fat.

07:22.165 --> 07:24.001
Like, supersized, okay?

07:24.034 --> 07:25.570
- A-And you know what really annoys me?
- What?

07:25.603 --> 07:28.105
When you guys see
we are from another country,

07:28.138 --> 07:30.874
you just speak louder
and slower to us.

07:30.907 --> 07:32.843
Maybe you guys should learn
another language.

07:32.876 --> 07:34.378
You know what I mean, partner?

08:21.925 --> 08:22.893
Aw.

08:36.006 --> 08:37.441
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

08:43.447 --> 08:44.947
Emilio.

09:07.504 --> 09:08.871
Okay?

09:39.034 --> 09:41.003
Okay, um...

10:25.782 --> 10:27.550
Okay.

10:49.271 --> 10:51.373
- Hey.
- Hola.

10:53.642 --> 10:55.277
Okay.

10:58.113 --> 11:00.115
Hi. This is Renato Murguia.

11:00.149 --> 11:02.051
- Hi.
- Hi.

11:02.084 --> 11:03.352
Uh, this is Katherine.

11:03.385 --> 11:05.254
Hi, Katherine.
How can I help you?

11:05.287 --> 11:07.256
I'm your father's wife.

11:10.459 --> 11:12.595
I'm calling because...

11:12.628 --> 11:17.266
well, I know your relationship
with him is complicated,

11:17.299 --> 11:21.136
but you should know
your father's very ill.

11:23.272 --> 11:25.241
Are you still there?

11:25.274 --> 11:27.243
Yes.

11:27.276 --> 11:29.545
It would mean so much
to your dad

11:29.578 --> 11:34.316
if you could come see him
here in Chicago.

11:34.350 --> 11:37.553
Um... listen, not to be rude,

11:37.586 --> 11:40.222
but I haven't heard
from him in years,

11:40.256 --> 11:43.225
and to be honest with you, um,

11:43.259 --> 11:46.362
I don't even see your husband
as my father anymore, so...

11:46.395 --> 11:50.266
Renato, he really needs
to see you.

11:58.507 --> 12:01.277
<i>¿Mamá?</i>

12:09.150 --> 12:10.519
No. No...

13:31.967 --> 13:33.534
Hey.

13:58.426 --> 14:01.229
<i>Welcome to
the United States of America.</i>

14:02.697 --> 14:05.400
"Ree-nae-doe"?

14:07.568 --> 14:10.304
It's pronounced "Re-naht-o."

14:10.338 --> 14:13.241
Oh, your accent is adorable.

14:13.274 --> 14:16.277
Welcome to America, friend.

14:16.310 --> 14:18.212
Where you from?

14:18.246 --> 14:19.681
Uh, from Mexico.

14:19.714 --> 14:22.350
- Oh, Mexico.
- Yes.

14:22.383 --> 14:24.485
I love that Cancún.

14:24.519 --> 14:26.988
The zip-lining down there,
it's amazing.

14:27.022 --> 14:29.490
If I lived in Mexico,
I'd zip-line every day.

14:29.524 --> 14:31.759
- Oh, yeah?
- You do a lot of zip-lining down there?

14:31.793 --> 14:33.461
I-I... No, I don't zip-line.

14:33.494 --> 14:35.229
- What?
- Yeah.

14:35.263 --> 14:38.232
Why do you live in Mexico, then?

14:45.540 --> 14:48.009
Mmm.

14:48.042 --> 14:49.444
Boomerang!

14:49.477 --> 14:51.579
Hold on, hold on. Boomerang!

14:53.748 --> 14:55.349
I can do this.

14:55.383 --> 14:56.684
Boomerang!
There we go. Hey.

14:56.718 --> 14:58.286
What's up, guys?
Asher is back.

14:58.319 --> 14:59.687
I'm live here
at the Boiler Monkey,

14:59.721 --> 15:02.623
and we're checking out
all these delish treats.

15:02.657 --> 15:04.726
But who is this?

15:04.759 --> 15:06.360
What's your name, partner?

15:06.394 --> 15:08.296
Please just don't film me.

15:08.329 --> 15:09.864
Oh, that's a cool accent, man.
Where you from?

15:09.897 --> 15:11.766
- From Mexico.
- Mexico?

15:11.799 --> 15:13.701
- Yes.
- Oh, that's dangerous. Is that why you fled here?

15:13.735 --> 15:15.436
I didn't flee here.

15:15.470 --> 15:17.304
Could you please take
that thing out my face?

15:17.338 --> 15:19.440
Yeah, okay,
you don't... Be calm, man.

15:19.474 --> 15:21.375
- I am calm.
- You don't need to be tense anymore.

15:21.409 --> 15:23.276
You're safe now.
You're in America.

15:23.310 --> 15:24.479
Next customer.

15:24.512 --> 15:25.513
All right.

15:26.514 --> 15:27.615
Hey there, "Beat-rice."

15:27.648 --> 15:28.816
It's Beatrice.

15:28.850 --> 15:31.552
Sure.

15:31.586 --> 15:33.755
I checked in on Yelp, so that
means that if I buy a coffee

15:33.788 --> 15:35.456
I can get anything else
for free, right?

15:35.490 --> 15:36.691
You can get another coffee
for free.

15:36.724 --> 15:38.826
Damn.

15:38.860 --> 15:40.695
Those doughnuts
look good, though.

15:41.729 --> 15:43.498
- What do you think?
- Just order.

15:43.531 --> 15:45.066
Okay. You know what?
I'll just have the two coffees,

15:45.099 --> 15:47.367
- and make one of them with almond milk.
- Okay.

15:47.400 --> 15:48.870
- That comes to $1.87.
- Great.

15:48.903 --> 15:51.072
Amigo, spot me two bucks?

15:51.105 --> 15:52.907
- What?
- Spot me two bucks?

15:52.940 --> 15:55.475
- No.
- You don't have two bucks?

15:55.509 --> 15:57.377
I do have two bucks, but I'm
not giving you any money.

15:57.410 --> 15:59.379
Ooh, what's your deal, man?
You know I'm good for it.

15:59.412 --> 16:00.882
- What's my deal? You don't carry any money on you?
- Yeah.

16:00.915 --> 16:03.316
Not even a-a credit card?

16:03.350 --> 16:04.819
No, all my liquid's tied up
in investments.

16:04.852 --> 16:06.888
Listen, if you can't afford
something, you can't buy it,

16:06.921 --> 16:09.456
so please move.

16:09.489 --> 16:11.692
Hi. I'm gonna have
a large coffee, please.

16:11.726 --> 16:13.761
Man, I-I didn't even
want the wall.

16:15.797 --> 16:17.664
You know what? I'm gonna buy

16:17.698 --> 16:19.499
all of these doughnuts,
and then I want you

16:19.533 --> 16:20.902
to throw them in the trash.

16:22.435 --> 16:24.471
You're-you're a monster.

16:24.504 --> 16:26.774
Yeah.
You can keep the change.

16:28.810 --> 16:30.510
Excuse me.

16:39.854 --> 16:41.388
Hi.

16:41.421 --> 16:43.657
I'm here to see Flavio Murguia.

16:43.690 --> 16:45.458
Renato?

16:50.998 --> 16:53.667
Hi. I'm Katherine.

16:53.700 --> 16:55.402
Thank you so much for coming.

16:58.605 --> 17:01.608
It's gonna mean so much
to your dad.

17:01.641 --> 17:03.777
He's been waiting for you.

17:16.690 --> 17:18.925
- I'll leave the two of you alone.
- Yes.

17:45.785 --> 17:47.520
Renato.

17:48.655 --> 17:51.524
Hola.

18:27.661 --> 18:30.497
Okay. Okay. Um...

18:31.731 --> 18:34.801
I want you to remember
this name,

18:34.834 --> 18:37.804
because it's gonna clear
a lot of things in your life.

18:39.572 --> 18:41.574
Eloise.

18:41.608 --> 18:43.977
It's all about Eloise.

18:46.913 --> 18:48.248
So, I was at the coffee shop,

18:48.281 --> 18:49.849
but they were all out
of coffee, so...

18:49.883 --> 18:51.517
- Are-are you following me?
- What are you doing here?

18:51.550 --> 18:53.053
- No. Why would I...
- What is wrong with you?

18:53.086 --> 18:53.820
- Are you following me?
- Dad, is-is this guy bothering you?

18:53.853 --> 18:55.755
Dad?

18:55.789 --> 18:59.726
Renato, meet your brother Asher.

19:01.527 --> 19:03.562
What? What do you...

19:03.595 --> 19:04.798
Wh-What do you mean, "brother"?
Th...

19:04.831 --> 19:06.565
This-this guy's a bully.
He is not nice.

19:06.598 --> 19:08.567
Please just-just...
just leave us for a second.

19:08.600 --> 19:10.036
No, no, why do I have to...
I'm not going.

19:10.070 --> 19:11.738
- Please just leave us. Leave.
- Dad, do I have to go?

19:11.771 --> 19:13.539
Please, I need you both
to hear this.

19:13.572 --> 19:15.607
Yeah.

19:16.642 --> 19:18.610
Look in my robe, my son.

19:27.653 --> 19:29.889
Ay, Renato.

19:29.923 --> 19:34.560
I wish I could just sit here
and explain everything to you,

19:34.593 --> 19:36.997
but they would just be words.

19:37.030 --> 19:39.732
You wouldn't understand.

19:39.765 --> 19:43.569
Certain things have to be seen
from a different perspective.

19:43.602 --> 19:46.039
Ah, I don't care about
your perspective at all.

19:46.072 --> 19:47.740
I just want to know
what happened.

19:47.773 --> 19:49.742
And you will.

19:49.775 --> 19:52.611
I promise you.

19:52.644 --> 19:57.716
All you need to do
is deliver this envelope.

19:57.750 --> 19:59.785
No.

19:59.818 --> 20:02.755
I'm not playing any of your...
of your games.

20:02.788 --> 20:04.023
If you don't want to tell me

20:04.057 --> 20:05.624
what happened,
I-I'm gonna leave.

20:05.657 --> 20:08.627
No. No, no, Renato.

20:08.660 --> 20:12.631
I know you hate me,
a-and I don't blame you,

20:12.664 --> 20:17.002
but I promise you
it will all make sense.

20:17.036 --> 20:19.004
I just need both of you
to promise me

20:19.038 --> 20:20.639
that you will deliver this.

20:20.672 --> 20:21.907
Why would I promise you
anything?

20:21.940 --> 20:23.776
I promise you, Dad.

20:24.810 --> 20:26.078
Renato, please.

20:26.111 --> 20:28.580
Please, there is so much
I want to tell you.

20:28.614 --> 20:30.682
Oh...

20:30.716 --> 20:33.052
I-I think...
I think I know enough.

20:33.085 --> 20:35.921
No. No, <i>mijo.</i>

20:36.922 --> 20:38.624
Goodbye, Flavio.

20:38.657 --> 20:40.360
<i>Por favor.</i>

20:40.393 --> 20:43.629
Renato, <i>mijo.</i>

20:52.704 --> 20:54.606
<i>¡Papá!</i>

21:05.184 --> 21:07.086
<i>Bueno.</i>

21:08.421 --> 21:10.789
Oh. Hi.

21:41.253 --> 21:42.955
Did you know Frank?

21:44.223 --> 21:45.991
- Sorry. Who?
- Frank.

21:46.024 --> 21:48.961
Katherine's husband.
Did you know him?

21:51.029 --> 21:53.132
No, I guess I didn't.

21:53.165 --> 21:56.201
Oh, he was a great man.

21:56.235 --> 21:58.904
So generous and caring, and...

21:58.937 --> 22:01.006
and he loved his family so much.

22:01.039 --> 22:02.640
Yeah.

22:04.276 --> 22:07.212
Uh, I'm sorry. I need to go.

22:09.982 --> 22:11.150
Hey.

22:12.251 --> 22:14.685
You know, I've been thinking
a lot about it,

22:14.719 --> 22:17.688
and I just want to let you know
I'm not mad at you anymore

22:17.722 --> 22:20.225
and I'm gonna give you
a second chance.

22:20.259 --> 22:23.095
Are you freaking kidding me
right now?

22:23.128 --> 22:25.830
- What? I'm apologizing here.
- Oh, yeah?

22:25.863 --> 22:28.033
Look, I guess it's kind of cool
I have a brother.

22:28.066 --> 22:29.301
Maybe I'll come down
to Mexico sometime

22:29.334 --> 22:30.969
and we can check out
these zip lines

22:31.003 --> 22:32.070
you guys keep bragging about.

22:32.104 --> 22:34.173
Shut up.

22:34.206 --> 22:36.008
I don't like you, okay?

22:36.041 --> 22:37.875
I don't want to be close to you.

22:37.909 --> 22:41.079
You're not my brother, so
please just stay away from me.

22:43.915 --> 22:46.218
- What are you doing, man?
- Oh, my God.

22:46.251 --> 22:48.220
We got to do this thing for Dad.

22:48.253 --> 22:50.322
Don't you even want to know
what the letter says?

22:50.355 --> 22:52.690
- No, I don't.
- I do.

22:55.793 --> 22:57.895
"My dear sons...

22:57.929 --> 23:00.165
"I know you have
many unanswered questions,

23:00.199 --> 23:01.999
"so you must go see
my friend Evaristo.

23:02.033 --> 23:04.303
"He will provide you with
the answers you are seeking.

23:04.336 --> 23:06.737
He will lead you to Eloise."

23:06.771 --> 23:08.773
Eloise. Holy shit, dude.
Do you think we have a sister?

23:08.806 --> 23:10.242
I really don't care.

23:10.275 --> 23:11.943
Hey, there's another envelope
in here. It's like a...

23:11.976 --> 23:13.811
It's like a clue.
I don't know if you know this,

23:13.844 --> 23:15.079
but Dad loved riddles.

23:15.112 --> 23:17.216
- Yeah.
- Hey!

23:18.149 --> 23:19.951
- Wait. Come on, man.
- "Ren-a-doo"?

23:19.984 --> 23:21.953
We're supposed to do this
together as brothers.

23:21.986 --> 23:23.522
You promised Dad
that we would do this.

23:23.555 --> 23:25.756
- No, I didn't promise him anything, okay?
- Yes.

23:25.790 --> 23:28.125
And do you really think
I want to go on a road trip

23:28.159 --> 23:31.796
with some stupid,
entitled shithead like you?

23:32.797 --> 23:34.899
Is this a trick question?

23:36.234 --> 23:38.970
Come on!

23:39.003 --> 23:40.304
What's your problem, man?

23:42.306 --> 23:43.975
<i>Bueno.</i>

24:28.085 --> 24:29.887
Okay.

24:38.429 --> 24:40.197
Come back to apologize?

24:40.231 --> 24:42.867
Pick me up tomorrow,
7:00 a.m., my hotel.

24:42.900 --> 24:44.402
Hell yeah. Road trip.

24:44.435 --> 24:47.038
No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
No road trip.

24:47.071 --> 24:48.306
Day trip, okay?

24:48.339 --> 24:50.875
7:00 a.m., my hotel, sharp.
You got it?

24:50.908 --> 24:52.143
- I got it.
- You got it?

24:52.176 --> 24:53.311
I got it. 7:00 a.m.

24:53.344 --> 24:55.212
- Jesus.
- Let's go.

25:10.494 --> 25:12.263
Yeah!

25:17.368 --> 25:19.370
Hey, hey.
What's up, <i>mi amigo?</i>

25:19.403 --> 25:21.939
- We said 7:00.
- I-I thought we said 8:00.

25:21.972 --> 25:23.140
No, I said 7:00.

25:23.174 --> 25:24.874
It must be the language barrier.

25:24.908 --> 25:26.843
I don't know.

25:36.354 --> 25:37.921
All right,
let's cut to the chase.

25:37.954 --> 25:39.190
You're wondering what those

25:39.223 --> 25:40.990
huge jugs of fuel are
back there, huh?

25:41.991 --> 25:44.128
They're carbon-based
alternative fuel.

25:44.161 --> 25:45.962
Okay. I'm assuming ethanol?

25:45.995 --> 25:47.931
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

25:47.964 --> 25:50.434
Hey, man, are you, like, smart?

25:50.468 --> 25:52.969
- I'm an engineer.
- Dude!

25:53.002 --> 25:54.305
Dad was an engineer.

25:54.338 --> 25:55.972
Did you know that?

25:56.005 --> 25:57.408
Yeah, man.

25:57.441 --> 25:59.943
Dad wanted me to be
an engineer, but I was like,

25:59.976 --> 26:01.679
"Yeah, no, thanks.
I'm not a loser."

26:01.712 --> 26:03.247
- Oh.
- I'm-I'm an ideas guy.

26:03.280 --> 26:05.316
- Oh, yeah? Yeah.
- You know what I mean? Yeah.

26:05.349 --> 26:06.983
I see.

26:07.016 --> 26:08.519
You're one of these
lazy Americans, right?

26:08.552 --> 26:11.121
No, I'm not... I'm not lazy.
I'm a... I'm a thoughts guy.

26:11.154 --> 26:12.456
Yeah, I can see. I can see.

26:12.490 --> 26:15.158
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

26:15.191 --> 26:17.328
- Do you have a job?
- What do you mean?

26:17.361 --> 26:19.262
I mean, do you have a job?
What do you do?

26:19.296 --> 26:20.398
I'm a brand ambassador.

26:20.431 --> 26:22.031
That's bullshit.

26:22.065 --> 26:23.933
Have you ever had a real job

26:23.967 --> 26:25.935
where someone actually paid you
for something?

26:25.969 --> 26:27.505
- Yeah, I've had a real job.
- Yeah? What?

26:27.538 --> 26:30.073
Yeah. I was a product
distribution specialist.

26:31.074 --> 26:33.377
What the hell is that?
What did you distribute?

26:33.411 --> 26:34.712
Hmm?

26:34.745 --> 26:36.146
Lots of stuff, man.

26:36.179 --> 26:38.281
Trip Dips, Awesome Blossoms,

26:38.314 --> 26:41.251
baby backs, ranch.
Lot of ranch.

26:41.284 --> 26:42.520
Are you talking about Chili's?

26:42.553 --> 26:44.287
Yeah.

26:44.320 --> 26:46.457
- You were a waiter at Chili's?
- Yeah.

26:46.490 --> 26:48.726
- Cool, huh?
- And what happened to that job?

26:48.759 --> 26:50.427
They had no vision.

26:50.460 --> 26:52.362
Oh, Chili's had no vision? Wow.

26:52.395 --> 26:54.164
- Yeah, they couldn't keep up, man.
- Yeah, that's great. Okay.

26:54.197 --> 26:55.965
It wasn't the right environment
for someone like me,

26:55.999 --> 26:57.167
with my talent and my ideas.
You know what I'm saying.

26:57.200 --> 26:59.035
- Can I ask you a huge favor?
- Yeah.

26:59.068 --> 27:00.437
Shut up! Okay?

27:00.470 --> 27:02.272
I don't want to
get to know you at all.

27:02.305 --> 27:04.274
