Okay, well, you should get one.

46:10.747 --> 46:11.882
It really helps
externalize emotions.

46:11.915 --> 46:13.149
Oh, yeah? Who told you that?

46:13.182 --> 46:14.317
Rebecca, my online therapist.

46:14.350 --> 46:15.318
- Oh, yeah?
- Yeah.

46:15.351 --> 46:16.453
Is it working for you?

46:16.486 --> 46:17.588
Well, just listen, okay?

46:17.621 --> 46:19.221
This is Emilio, all right?

46:19.255 --> 46:21.123
<i>Papá.</i>

46:21.157 --> 46:23.493
Math is super hard.
I never get the answers right,

46:23.527 --> 46:25.394
and the kids call me <i>estúpido.</i>

46:25.428 --> 46:27.296
So, what, my-my kid
is Russian now?

46:27.330 --> 46:29.098
Come on. Take care of him.

46:33.770 --> 46:35.672
Okay, listen, Emilio.

46:35.706 --> 46:37.473
- No, no, to the puppet.
- Okay, listen, Emilio.

46:37.506 --> 46:39.508
The only reason
kids are making fun of you

46:39.542 --> 46:41.544
is because you let them, okay?

46:41.577 --> 46:43.379
And math is all about practice.

46:43.412 --> 46:45.481
You just need to buckle up
and do the work. That's it.

46:45.514 --> 46:47.350
But will you
help me do the work, Papá?

46:47.383 --> 46:49.619
No! No, you-you need to learn
to do everything by yourself

46:49.653 --> 46:51.387
because no one's gonna help you.

46:51.420 --> 46:53.122
No one is gonna help you ever.

46:56.359 --> 46:57.693
Hey, stop. No.

46:57.728 --> 46:59.595
<i>¡Papá!! Ay, no!</i>

47:01.530 --> 47:04.300
Wow. Your
stepson was just hit by a semi.

47:04.333 --> 47:05.401
I don't care.

47:07.771 --> 47:09.438
<i>You excited to meet our sister?</i>

47:09.472 --> 47:11.240
<i>Shut up.</i>

47:16.479 --> 47:19.348
Are you Eloise?

47:20.750 --> 47:22.652
Uh, hi.

47:22.685 --> 47:25.454
Uh, Flavio Murguia sent us.

47:27.490 --> 47:28.658
Mm, great.

47:28.691 --> 47:30.593
He doesn't like you, either.

47:30.626 --> 47:32.261
Excuse me. Sir?

47:33.295 --> 47:35.531
Your dad's had me hold on
to this for a while now.

47:35.564 --> 47:37.700
Said one day
somebody would come for it.

47:42.838 --> 47:44.640
This is my father's
wedding ring.

47:45.608 --> 47:48.344
I'm here to see
that he pawned it off?

47:48.377 --> 47:50.279
No.

47:50.312 --> 47:52.748
You're here to understand how
it got here in the first place.

47:54.283 --> 47:56.385
- Did you know our dad?
- I did.

47:56.419 --> 47:58.688
He was an easy man to like.

47:58.721 --> 48:00.690
We've stayed in touch
over the years.

48:00.723 --> 48:03.993
Oh. I'm glad to see
that he kept in touch with you.

48:04.026 --> 48:05.795
Listen, it's been a long ride,

48:05.828 --> 48:07.563
and I really need
some answers, so...

48:07.596 --> 48:09.532
Maybe you ought to learn
to shut your mouth

48:09.565 --> 48:11.333
and listen to the story.

48:11.367 --> 48:13.502
Ooh-wee, I like this guy.

48:13.536 --> 48:17.606
Must've been
at least 20 years ago now.

48:17.640 --> 48:20.276
One day, that front door opens,

48:20.309 --> 48:22.778
and this man comes stumbling in
all beat to hell.

48:22.812 --> 48:25.014
Hey, hey.

48:25.047 --> 48:26.782
You looking for trouble,
you've come to the wrong place.

48:26.816 --> 48:27.817
You understand?

48:27.850 --> 48:29.418
No, no, no. I'm sorry, sir.

48:29.452 --> 48:32.421
Please.
I-I'm not here to rob you.

48:32.455 --> 48:35.357
I just need enough
for a bus ticket, please.

48:35.391 --> 48:37.727
I-I'll sell you
everything I have.

48:37.760 --> 48:39.729
Okay? Just take it.

48:39.762 --> 48:43.231
I can't sell any of this.
No, no, no, don't. I...

48:44.700 --> 48:46.502
- Take it.
- No, I-I can't sell any of this.

48:49.605 --> 48:50.740
Please.

48:50.773 --> 48:53.476
Take it all.

48:53.509 --> 48:56.311
The ring.
I can sell the ring.

48:59.782 --> 49:01.784
So, what happened to him?

49:01.817 --> 49:03.418
What you need to know

49:03.452 --> 49:05.386
is that all your father
cared about

49:05.420 --> 49:07.656
was getting back
to his family in Mexico.

49:07.690 --> 49:10.659
<i>So, with the little money
he had,</i>

49:10.693 --> 49:14.329
<i>he bought a bus ticket to
the border in El Paso, Texas.</i>

49:14.362 --> 49:16.866
Bus leaves in 15 minutes.

49:16.899 --> 49:20.803
<i>That bus stopped
here in Oklahoma City.</i>

49:37.720 --> 49:39.487
Get the money.

49:39.521 --> 49:40.455
Get the money.

49:40.488 --> 49:41.757
Here, go.

49:47.695 --> 49:49.364
Where you going?

49:50.665 --> 49:51.867
<i>But then they took the thing</i>

49:51.901 --> 49:53.668
<i>that he cared about the most.</i>

49:54.904 --> 49:56.738
His only way home.

49:59.942 --> 50:02.677
The ring.
I can sell the ring.

50:07.983 --> 50:09.818
No. No, no, no.

50:09.852 --> 50:11.120
Please.

50:12.587 --> 50:14.322
I beg you.

50:15.557 --> 50:17.358
Okay, look.

50:17.392 --> 50:19.727
I'll make a deal with you,
all right?

50:19.761 --> 50:22.463
I will personally buy
the ring from you.

50:23.498 --> 50:24.766
Just me.

50:24.799 --> 50:27.702
And I will hold on to it
for you for 90 days.

50:27.735 --> 50:29.470
Okay?
I promise I won't sell it.

50:29.504 --> 50:30.605
No one.

50:30.638 --> 50:31.873
Promise.

50:31.906 --> 50:34.843
You come back
and bring me the money...

50:34.876 --> 50:37.645
the-the same price
as the ring, okay?

50:37.679 --> 50:39.547
And it's yours.

50:43.751 --> 50:46.821
<i>And once he finally got
all the way to El Paso,</i>

50:46.855 --> 50:50.692
<i>it was just a long walk home
to the border.</i>

50:55.530 --> 50:57.799
You're about to enter Mexico.

51:16.517 --> 51:18.820
Hold it right there, sir.
Don't move.

51:18.853 --> 51:20.989
Hands in the air.
Hands in the air, sir.

51:21.022 --> 51:22.757
Please.

51:22.790 --> 51:24.959
I-I'm just trying to get back
to my family.

51:24.993 --> 51:26.794
- Why is there blood on you?
- Whose blood is that?

51:26.828 --> 51:28.997
Please, I-I just want
to see my son.

51:29.030 --> 51:31.399
I said keep your hands up.

51:38.239 --> 51:40.041
I'm coming for you, boy!

51:40.074 --> 51:41.609
What you looking at?

51:43.544 --> 51:46.047
<i>They put your dad
in general population.</i>

51:53.955 --> 51:56.658
<i>Your father was stuck there.</i>

51:56.691 --> 51:58.226
<i>No one was coming for him,</i>

51:58.259 --> 52:01.796
<i>because no one even knew
he was there.</i>

52:01.829 --> 52:03.965
And he was in there a long time.

52:05.532 --> 52:08.036
<i>And that's when he got sick.</i>

52:08.069 --> 52:09.804
<i>Real sick.</i>

52:13.741 --> 52:15.542
Dump him. Dump him.

52:26.754 --> 52:28.723
This is the second time

52:28.756 --> 52:31.525
I've had to hold on
to this ring.

52:31.558 --> 52:32.961
It belongs to you now.

52:32.994 --> 52:36.764
But... but what happened
after that?

52:36.798 --> 52:38.800
Why didn't he come back?

52:43.570 --> 52:45.006
I'm done with this.

52:54.548 --> 52:56.516
Yo, what are you doing, man?

52:56.550 --> 52:58.585
I'm going home.
I'm done with this.

52:58.618 --> 53:00.587
Dude, you can't leave now.
Look.

53:00.620 --> 53:02.522
- Eloise.
- Oh, wow.

53:02.556 --> 53:04.025
Don't you want to know
how the story ends?

53:04.058 --> 53:06.995
Oh, I know how it ends.
I know how it ends.

53:07.028 --> 53:09.763
He doesn't come back.

53:09.796 --> 53:12.733
He cheats on me and my mom
with some American woman,

53:12.766 --> 53:15.036
has you and starts
a whole new life here.

53:15.069 --> 53:16.837
- That's it.
- No, that can't be the whole story.

53:16.870 --> 53:18.006
Come on, don't you want
the real answer?

53:18.039 --> 53:20.741
I got the answer, okay?!

53:20.774 --> 53:22.642
He forgot about me.

53:22.676 --> 53:25.012
That's it. He didn't die.

53:25.046 --> 53:28.316
Everything we're hearing about
was 25 years ago.

53:28.349 --> 53:29.916
What was he doing since then?

53:29.950 --> 53:31.952
Because he-he certainly wasn't
thinking about me.

53:31.985 --> 53:33.887
That whole story was
about him trying

53:33.920 --> 53:35.922
- to get back to you. He didn't...
- Oh, whatever.

53:35.956 --> 53:37.991
- He didn't forget about you.
- Excuses, excuses, man.

53:38.025 --> 53:40.761
I don't care, okay?
I-I have a life to go back to.

53:40.794 --> 53:42.863
I-I have a family.

53:42.896 --> 53:44.598
What's that supposed to mean?

53:44.631 --> 53:46.099
That means that
you're not my family.

53:46.133 --> 53:49.102
Okay? You're not my brother.
You mean nothing to me.

53:51.738 --> 53:53.073
Move, please. Move!

53:53.106 --> 53:54.641
Hey, don't bully him. He's...

53:54.674 --> 53:56.843
Move, Asher! Jesus.

53:56.877 --> 53:58.979
Hey, I meant what I said.

53:59.012 --> 54:00.881
You're gonna be
a terrible father.

54:00.914 --> 54:02.916
And you know what else?
You're a terrible son.

54:02.949 --> 54:04.985
Yeah, have a nice life.

54:12.159 --> 54:13.960
So, where you from?

54:17.398 --> 54:19.699
Hi. I'm gonna take
the first flight to Mexico City

54:19.733 --> 54:21.868
or whatever gets me the hell
out of this goddamn country.

54:23.770 --> 54:25.072
You're gonna have to
try that again.

54:25.105 --> 54:26.907
Is that how you speak
to your mother?

54:26.940 --> 54:29.042
I'm getting married
tomorrow, okay?

54:29.076 --> 54:31.678
And you better watch your tone
when you're talking to me.

54:31.711 --> 54:32.979
Okay.

54:33.013 --> 54:34.147
Now apologize.

54:34.181 --> 54:36.216
Fuck. What?

54:36.249 --> 54:38.085
Apologize.

54:39.786 --> 54:41.855
Apologize.

54:43.824 --> 54:45.892
I... I apologize.

54:45.926 --> 54:48.095
I apologize. I apologize.

54:48.128 --> 54:49.763
- Now, passport, please.
- Yes.

54:49.796 --> 54:51.731
Whatever you need, ma'am.
Whatever you need.

54:54.134 --> 54:55.836
Shit.

54:55.869 --> 54:58.705
I... I left it in the car.

54:58.738 --> 55:00.207
But I-I have a photo

55:00.240 --> 55:01.842
of my passport in my phone here.

55:01.875 --> 55:03.210
I would really love
to help you, but, honey,

55:03.243 --> 55:04.845
you ain't flying nowhere
without a passport.

55:04.878 --> 55:06.146
I need to get into that flight.

55:06.179 --> 55:08.748
Please, please
help me out here. Please.

55:10.817 --> 55:12.986
All right.
Here's what you do.

55:13.019 --> 55:14.821
- Yeah.
- Take out your phone.

55:14.855 --> 55:16.189
- Okay.
- Dial this number.

55:16.223 --> 55:18.725
- 1-800...
- Yeah?

55:18.758 --> 55:20.727
I don't give a shit!

55:20.760 --> 55:22.229
Find someone who cares.

55:22.262 --> 55:24.965
- Next customer.
- Shit!

55:29.803 --> 55:32.906
I can't, I can't,
I...

55:36.042 --> 55:38.777
Assholes Anonymous.
How may I help you?

55:40.147 --> 55:42.282
You're very funny.
That was very funny.

55:42.315 --> 55:44.084
Sometimes you're very funny.

55:44.117 --> 55:47.686
Listen, uh, I have
a small problem here, and, um,

55:47.720 --> 55:50.257
I...

55:50.290 --> 55:52.858
I really need your...
I really need your help.

55:52.892 --> 55:54.027
You're gonna have to speak up.

55:54.060 --> 55:55.228
I can't...
No, I can't hear you.

55:55.262 --> 55:57.696
I said I...
I really need your help.

55:57.730 --> 55:59.299
Can you hear him? I can't hear him.

55:59.332 --> 56:02.302
I really need your help, man.

56:14.813 --> 56:16.283
Okay, uh, I'm sorry.

56:16.316 --> 56:19.319
Okay? I-I...
I owe you an apology.

56:19.352 --> 56:22.222
The things I said back there,
I didn't mean it, okay?

56:22.255 --> 56:24.324
I'm sorry, and...

56:24.357 --> 56:27.026
I'm actually surprised
you-you come to pick me up.

56:27.059 --> 56:28.295
What are you talking about?

56:28.328 --> 56:30.062
What I'm...
what I'm talking about?

56:30.095 --> 56:31.298
Yeah.

56:31.331 --> 56:33.866
Well, why did you come
pick me up?

56:33.899 --> 56:35.935
'Cause, man,

56:35.968 --> 56:37.703
we're brothers.

56:39.038 --> 56:40.839
And don't you worry, bro.

56:40.873 --> 56:42.309
We're gonna get you to El Paso,

56:42.342 --> 56:45.512
and we're gonna re-sneak you
across that border.

56:45.545 --> 56:48.147
You'll be back for your wedding
in no time.

56:48.180 --> 56:49.949
Ain't that right, Renatito?

57:03.128 --> 57:04.830
You want something?

57:04.863 --> 57:06.265
Seaweed crisps.

57:08.968 --> 57:11.036
Come on. Come on.

57:11.070 --> 57:12.137
Come on.

57:12.171 --> 57:14.340
Hey.

57:14.373 --> 57:16.008
Hi.

57:16.041 --> 57:17.843
Look at this freak show.

57:17.876 --> 57:20.980
Hey. That your dog,
or is you just playing with it?

57:21.013 --> 57:23.282
It's okay. Don't worry.

57:23.315 --> 57:25.384
- Don't worry.
- Hey, you deaf, boy? Hey.

57:25.417 --> 57:27.353
They got the same calves.

57:27.386 --> 57:29.855
- You deaf?
- What you doing with that goat?

57:29.888 --> 57:31.257
Oh, that's love right there.

57:31.290 --> 57:32.992
Aw, aren't they cute?

57:33.025 --> 57:34.293
Run, boy, run.

57:34.326 --> 57:37.229
- Looks like he's gonna cry.
- Hey. Hey.

57:38.397 --> 57:41.166
Hey!

57:41.200 --> 57:42.801
Freak.

57:42.835 --> 57:43.936
Oh!

58:02.855 --> 58:04.957
What happened back there?

58:06.191 --> 58:08.227
What were those guys
saying to you?

58:08.260 --> 58:10.162
It was nothing, man.

58:10.195 --> 58:12.197
Didn't look like nothing.

58:13.299 --> 58:16.835
You shouldn't let people
treat you like that, you know?

58:16.869 --> 58:18.337
- It doesn't bother me.
- Oh, really?

58:18.370 --> 58:20.205
- No.
- Okay.

58:20.239 --> 58:22.074
People always make fun
of other people

58:22.107 --> 58:24.877
because they think
they're different.

58:24.910 --> 58:26.879
But they're not.

58:26.912 --> 58:29.448
I'm not different.

58:29.481 --> 58:33.952
Well, being different is not
a bad thing, you know?

58:35.154 --> 58:37.423
Nah, I know.

58:37.456 --> 58:39.958
All right.

58:43.162 --> 58:44.829
Oh.

58:45.464 --> 58:47.166
You didn't open this.

58:47.199 --> 58:49.201
We always open 'em together.

58:49.234 --> 58:51.836
- Can I?
- Yeah.

58:53.038 --> 58:56.141
Huh. Saint Mary's Convent.

58:56.175 --> 58:57.409
- Look at this.
- Whoa.

58:57.443 --> 58:59.144
Dude, do you think
our sister's a nun?

58:59.178 --> 59:01.380
Hey, wait.
What does that make us?

59:01.413 --> 59:02.947
Um, nothing.

59:02.980 --> 59:04.316
Oh.

59:04.350 --> 59:06.285
El Paso, Texas.

59:06.318 --> 59:08.187
El Paso?

59:08.220 --> 59:10.021
Come on, dude. Come on.

59:10.054 --> 59:12.023
Let's see if you can
take us there in time.

59:12.056 --> 59:13.958
Watch this.

59:29.408 --> 59:32.378
What's that? What's happening?

59:32.411 --> 59:35.012
What's happening?

59:37.282 --> 59:39.016
We're out of gas.

59:42.554 --> 59:45.056
- Are you kidding me right now?
- Hmm-mm.

59:46.057 --> 59:47.359
We are in the mid...
That was your only

59:47.393 --> 59:48.993
responsibility, dude.

59:49.026 --> 59:50.261
Why are you laughing?
Are you stupid?

59:50.294 --> 59:52.096
I love watching you
freak out, man.

59:52.130 --> 59:54.298
This is why I keep extra fuel
in the back.

59:54.332 --> 59:56.402
I'm pretty responsible, man.

1:00:00.238 --> 1:00:03.274
Oh, Renatito, no.

1:00:03.307 --> 1:00:04.443
Renatito, no.

1:00:04.476 --> 1:00:06.177
- That is a naughty boy.
- Ah!

1:00:06.210 --> 1:00:08.012
- Oh, my God, I knew it!
- Hold on.

1:00:08.045 --> 1:00:09.715
- Hold on.
- Hold on?!

1:00:09.748 --> 1:00:11.550
I'm gonna kill that thing
when you're not looking, okay?!

1:00:11.583 --> 1:00:13.217
Don't bully him, man.

1:00:13.251 --> 1:00:15.019
I'm not joking!
I'm gonna kill that thing!

1:00:15.052 --> 1:00:17.054
We eat those things in Mexico.
They're very tasty!

1:00:17.088 --> 1:00:19.290
- Hey, he can hear you, asshole.
- You stupid...

1:00:20.592 --> 1:00:22.293
Okay, okay.

1:00:22.326 --> 1:00:23.529
You're stronger.
You're stronger.

1:00:26.397 --> 1:00:28.366
I'm sorry I punched you, okay?

1:00:28.399 --> 1:00:30.968
Ah, it's all right.
Brothers fight, man.

1:00:31.002 --> 1:00:33.271
- That's how we show love.
- Don't start with that, please.

1:00:33.304 --> 1:00:34.405
Hey, look.

1:00:34.439 --> 1:00:36.541
Oh, my God. Oh...

1:00:36.574 --> 1:00:38.943
Please have a phone.

1:00:41.078 --> 1:00:42.580
Jesus.

1:00:55.460 --> 1:00:57.428
Yes!

1:00:57.462 --> 1:00:59.497
Oh, shit. It's death.

1:00:59.530 --> 1:01:00.565
"It's death"?

1:01:00.598 --> 1:01:02.200
I mean...

1:01:02.233 --> 1:01:04.035
it's dead.
I mean it's-it's not working.

1:01:05.069 --> 1:01:07.371
Ooh, well, what do we have here?

1:01:08.473 --> 1:01:10.241
What are these things?

1:01:10.274 --> 1:01:11.409
I don't know.

1:01:11.442 --> 1:01:12.477
It smells like Grandma.

1:01:12.510 --> 1:01:14.245
It's moonshine.

1:01:15.379 --> 1:01:16.581
It's-it's pure alcohol.

1:01:16.614 --> 1:01:18.349
Oh, keep it away from me.

1:01:18.382 --> 1:01:20.551
One sip of pinot,
and whoo-wee, I'm out.

1:01:20.585 --> 1:01:23.287
That's it.

1:01:23.321 --> 1:01:26.090
We can make ethanol out of this.

1:01:26.123 --> 1:01:27.592
All we got to do is purify it,

1:01:27.625 --> 1:01:30.194
and then we can use that
to fuel your car.

1:01:30.228 --> 1:01:33.130
See? You are
a great engineer, man.

1:01:33.164 --> 1:01:35.032
Stop doubting yourself.

1:01:41.272 --> 1:01:43.508
Okay. That's it.

1:01:43.541 --> 1:01:45.343
Okay. Okay, here we go.

1:01:45.376 --> 1:01:48.179
Why are you sweating so much?

1:01:48.212 --> 1:01:49.480
I'm a little nervous.

1:01:49.514 --> 1:01:51.382
Okay, give me that.

1:01:51.415 --> 1:01:53.184
Where'd you...
where'd you find these, anyway?

1:01:53.217 --> 1:01:54.519
In the creepy drawer
next to the animal teeth.

1:01:54.552 --> 1:01:56.153
Okay. Listen.

1:01:56.187 --> 1:01:58.389
We need to be very fast
with this, okay?

1:01:58.422 --> 1:02:01.057
None of the ethanol vapors
can get out.

1:02:01.091 --> 1:02:02.827
- You got it? You got it?
- I got it.

1:02:02.860 --> 1:02:04.829
- The ethanol. The vapors.
- Yes.

