1:20:18.315 --> 1:20:20.217
<i>I got this feeling.</i>

1:20:20.250 --> 1:20:22.252
<i>Uh, something inside me</i>

1:20:22.286 --> 1:20:25.489
just couldn't let me
cross over for good

1:20:25.522 --> 1:20:28.325
<i>until I apologized to her.</i>

1:20:28.359 --> 1:20:31.295
<i>I had no idea how my life
was about to change.</i>

1:20:55.753 --> 1:20:58.656
<i>This baby was in danger.</i>

1:21:06.230 --> 1:21:08.732
<i>I could never blame her
for not accepting my apology.</i>

1:21:08.766 --> 1:21:12.302
But I already went through the
pain of leaving one son behind.

1:21:13.470 --> 1:21:15.272
<i>I couldn't do it to another.</i>

1:22:02.319 --> 1:22:04.253
Flavio.

1:22:40.924 --> 1:22:42.659
<i>This was all my fault,</i>

1:22:42.693 --> 1:22:44.828
not hers.

1:22:44.862 --> 1:22:47.296
You have to realize

1:22:47.330 --> 1:22:49.465
your mother was just trying
to protect you.

1:22:49.499 --> 1:22:51.501
And I thought it would be
easier for you

1:22:51.534 --> 1:22:53.269
if you just slowly...

1:22:54.537 --> 1:22:56.707
...forgot about me.

1:22:57.875 --> 1:23:00.276
<i>I should have done more.</i>

1:23:02.512 --> 1:23:06.349
<i>I should have just found a way
to come see you.</i>

1:23:07.350 --> 1:23:09.820
<i>Ay, Renato, mijo.</i>

1:23:11.554 --> 1:23:14.323
I want you to know
how special you were to me.

1:23:16.392 --> 1:23:18.728
You were the love of my life.

1:23:21.564 --> 1:23:24.567
And I have to live
with this guilt every day.

1:23:24.600 --> 1:23:26.103
But you,

1:23:26.136 --> 1:23:28.738
<i>you are the one
who has suffered the most.</i>

1:23:28.771 --> 1:23:32.876
In some kind of way, I...
I tried to make up for it

1:23:32.910 --> 1:23:36.813
by putting all my energy
into you, Asher.

1:23:36.846 --> 1:23:40.416
I wanted to be
such a good father to you,

1:23:40.449 --> 1:23:44.687
but I failed you, too, didn't I?

1:23:44.720 --> 1:23:47.690
<i>In my small, simple mind,</i>

1:23:47.723 --> 1:23:51.594
<i>I tried to recapture with you
what I had with Renato.</i>

1:23:51.627 --> 1:23:54.430
<i>But, Asher, you were so...</i>

1:23:54.463 --> 1:23:55.598
unique.

1:24:04.006 --> 1:24:07.510
<i>And I didn't know
how to connect with you.</i>

1:24:09.979 --> 1:24:14.450
<i>So, instead, I pulled away...</i>

1:24:14.483 --> 1:24:16.586
<i>for far too long.</i>

1:24:21.490 --> 1:24:22.625
<i>Asher,</i>

1:24:22.658 --> 1:24:25.695
my sweet, beautiful boy,

1:24:25.728 --> 1:24:28.164
I am so sorry it took me so long

1:24:28.198 --> 1:24:30.867
to see there was never
anything wrong with you.

1:24:34.804 --> 1:24:36.839
I want you to know

1:24:36.873 --> 1:24:38.908
I never gave up on you.

1:24:39.909 --> 1:24:41.611
Never.

1:24:42.612 --> 1:24:45.815
Asher, you have
such a caring heart.

1:24:46.816 --> 1:24:49.485
This world needs you so much.

1:24:49.518 --> 1:24:53.589
You're going to do so much good
with everybody you touch.

1:24:54.991 --> 1:24:57.660
I made both of you feel

1:24:57.693 --> 1:24:59.896
like you were not
the son I wanted,

1:24:59.929 --> 1:25:01.797
but in truth...

1:25:03.599 --> 1:25:05.701
...I was not the father
you deserved.

1:25:05.735 --> 1:25:10.039
And I know there's nothing
I can do to make up for it...

1:25:11.641 --> 1:25:13.676
...but I still felt
I had to try.

1:25:14.677 --> 1:25:18.413
<i>So, when life decided to
throw me one last curveball...</i>

1:25:20.482 --> 1:25:23.619
<i>...I decided to put
this whole trip together.</i>

1:25:25.554 --> 1:25:28.523
<i>To put my two boys together.</i>

1:25:29.959 --> 1:25:31.661
Because my hope is

1:25:31.694 --> 1:25:34.830
<i>that even though
it might seem like I'm gone,</i>

1:25:34.864 --> 1:25:38.566
<i>we could still do this together.</i>

1:25:39.902 --> 1:25:42.604
My biggest regret
is not being able

1:25:42.638 --> 1:25:46.809
to share this final journey
with you.

1:25:46.842 --> 1:25:50.012
And even though
I'm no longer here,

1:25:50.046 --> 1:25:53.950
please know I am always with you

1:25:53.983 --> 1:25:57.720
and I am always
watching over you both.

1:26:01.958 --> 1:26:03.692
Wait.

1:26:03.725 --> 1:26:05.962
What-what last journey?

1:26:05.995 --> 1:26:08.563
What is he talking about?

1:26:08.596 --> 1:26:10.066
With Eloise.

1:26:11.067 --> 1:26:13.102
- What?
- What? S...

1:26:13.135 --> 1:26:15.037
So, there is an Eloise?

1:26:16.038 --> 1:26:17.672
Would you like to see her?

1:27:24.039 --> 1:27:25.874
What are you thinking about?

1:27:28.176 --> 1:27:31.079
The way I left him
in the hospital.

1:27:34.115 --> 1:27:36.584
I didn't even
say goodbye to him.

1:27:38.987 --> 1:27:41.089
I didn't... I didn't even...

1:27:41.122 --> 1:27:42.724
- tell him...
- He knew.

1:27:44.826 --> 1:27:46.161
He knew.

1:27:46.194 --> 1:27:47.929
Yeah.

1:27:59.741 --> 1:28:02.811
Well...
you got a wedding to catch.

1:28:02.844 --> 1:28:05.814
- Yeah. Yes, I do.
- Yeah. Yeah.

1:28:21.096 --> 1:28:22.997
Thanks, Asher.

1:28:23.031 --> 1:28:24.833
For everything.

1:28:42.150 --> 1:28:43.785
Fly safe, amigo.

1:29:27.794 --> 1:29:30.231
I know.

1:29:32.100 --> 1:29:34.202
Hey!

1:29:35.936 --> 1:29:37.272
What's wrong?
What's going on?

1:29:37.305 --> 1:29:39.006
Uh...

1:29:39.040 --> 1:29:40.941
We need to get you a suit.

1:29:42.177 --> 1:29:44.978
I can't get married
without my brothers.

1:31:03.156 --> 1:31:05.292
<i>If you were to ask me now</i>

1:31:05.325 --> 1:31:07.894
<i>if a father and son
should be best friends,</i>

1:31:07.928 --> 1:31:09.796
<i>I would say...</i>

1:31:09.830 --> 1:31:11.965
<i>of course they should.</i>

1:31:41.028 --> 1:31:42.863
Ooh.
